tourBios.curYrHigh: Joined PGA TOUR Latinoamérica with a T9 finish at the Sebring, FL Q-School in January. Lost a six-man playoff for three spots that secured exempt status for the first half of the Latin American season.
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Finished T39 at the Florida Qualifying Tournament, earning conditional status for the Mackenzie Tour's season. Had three missed cuts and a withdrawal in four starts in Canada.

2011-13: Played on the Dakotas Tour.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played college golf for the University of Wisconsin–Parkside, an NCAA Division II school... Named All-GLVC Conference in 2010.... Won the Wisconsin State Championship in 2006 and was named All-State three times while at Mequon Homestead HS.
tourBios.personal: Has one brother, Bobby... Attended Mequon Homestead High School... His biggest thrill on golf was making a hole in one on Father's Day with his father as witness... Hidden Glen at Bahle Farms is his favorite golf course... Big Milwaukee Bucks, Green Bay Packers fan… Star Wars and the Bourne Trilogy are his favorite movies... Personal motto is: “Nothing but the best”... Carries a 1914 dime for good luck... Saw the 1996 Chicago Bulls win their 70th game and says that has been the best single sporting event he has ever attended.
